Class Description
ActiveData

True if the crime incident resulted in an arrest being made.

Block

CrimeRecord
CrimeRecord stores the categorical data associated with a record of a crime.

A TimeSeriesGraph type used to plot a graph of number of crime records over time.
CSVExporter
A crime data exporter used to export crime data to CSV file format.
CSVImporter
A crime data importer used to import crime data from CSV files.
DataCategory
This class facilitates the selection of the various categories within a CrimeRecord, providing the methods setCategoryValue and getCategoryValue for setting and getting the value of an attribute of a CrimeRecord instance through the corresponding DataCategory.

DataExporter

An abstract class providing an interface for importing crime data from a supported file type.

Graph
A superclass specifying all methods which a Graph type must implement in order to interface with control classes.

A controller for a dialogue box which is shown when graph options are not in a valid configuration for plotting.

UnsupportedCategoryException
This exception type is thrown when a process tries to perform an operation on or using data from a category that is unsupported, or when trying to add data to an attribute corresponding to a DataCategory which is unsupported or does not exist.
UnsupportedFileTypeException
This exception type is thrown when trying to import a file which has an unsupported file format.
Ward
